```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt, bump = 3)
    if !isa(dt, DateTime))
        error("Input must be of type DateTime.")
    end

    return dt + Hours(bump)
end
```
In this implementation, the `timezone_bumper` function takes a `DateTime` input and an optional `bump` parameter (defaulting to 3 hours). The function checks if the input is a `DateTime`, throwing an error for `Date` types. Finally, it adds the specified number of hours to the timestamp.
